# Plannotator Workflow (Cursor)

`plannotator-annotate` and `plannotator-review` skills own CLI invocation and response handling. This rule covers only what Cursor lacks vs Claude Code.

## Plan Mode

After Cursor writes a plan to its default path under `~/.cursor/plans/`, before implementation:

1. Invoke `plannotator-annotate` on that plan file with `--gate --json`.
2. Do not implement until the skill reports approval.

Use the plan file Cursor created — do not move plans to a different directory.

## Code Review

Follow the Code Review Workflow procedure in `AGENTS.md` (repo root). The full procedure is defined there; this rule supplements it with Cursor-specific invocation details.

To invoke the Plannotator code review interface, run `plannotator review` in the terminal.

After review returns no feedback (approved), run `touch /tmp/.plannotator-reviewed` to unlock the commit gate. Then `git add` remaining changes and `git commit`.
